  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What is the process of securing admission at MICA, Ahmedabad?",
  "response": "Securing admission at the Mudra Institute of Communications, Ahmedabad (MICA) involves several steps. The process mainly applies to candidates seeking to enroll in the Post Graduate Diploma in Management - Communications (PGDM-C) program, among other courses. Here's a general outline of the admission process:\n\n1. **Eligibility Criteria**:\n   - Candidates must have a bachelor\u2019s degree in any discipline from a recognized university.\n   - It's advisable to check the specific eligibility criteria for the course you are interested in, as it may vary.\n\n2. **Entrance Exam**:\n   - Candidates are required to take one of the national-level entrance exams like CAT (Common Admission Test), XAT (Xavier Admission Test), or GMAT (Graduate Management Admission Test). MICA also has its own entrance exam known as the MICA Admission Test (MICAT).\n   - Some applicants may also take the GMAT in case they are from the NRI category.\n\n3. **MICAT**:\n   - Candidates must register and appear for MICAT, which tests both cognitive and non-cognitive skills.\n   - MICAT typically includes sections on verbal ability, quantitative ability, general awareness, and divergent-convergent thinking.\n\n4. **Shortlisting for Group Exercise and Personal Interview**:\n   - Based on the performance in MICAT and the entrance exam scores (CAT/XAT/GMAT), candidates will be shortlisted for the next stage.\n   - The selection process usually involves a Group Exercise (GE) and Personal Interview (PI) conducted by MICA.\n\n5. **Final Selection**:\n   - The final admission list is based on the candidate's performance in the entrance exam (CAT/XAT/GMAT), MICAT, GE, and PI, along with academic background and work experience.\n   - MICA has its specific weightage for each component as part of the selection criteria.\n\n6. **Application Process**:\n   - Candidates must fill out the online application form available on the MICA website within the specified timeline.\n   - Required documents, including academic records, entrance exam scores, and other relevant certificates, must be submitted.\n\n7. **Fees and Enrollment**:\n   - Once selected, candidates must confirm their admission by paying the required fees within the given timeframe.\n\n8. **Orientation**:\n   - After enrollment, candidates are typically required to attend an orientation program which provides an overview of the curriculum and student life at MICA.\n\nIt's important to regularly check MICA's official website for the most current information about application deadlines, eligibility criteria, and any changes to the admission process, as these can vary from year to year.",
